children.subject:
This is for EECS16A and I'm first year, undeclared at L&S

Will I get off the waitlist anytime before classes start in Sp ?

history.content:
Generally speaking, the reserve capacities are set for EECS classes to expire at the end of phase 2 enrollments. The system then automatically fills any open seats based solely on your wait list position.

I have no idea if this class will expand in the future since I manage the CompSci classes and not EECS or ELENG classes.

I got an email titled :

"Enrollment Update: Can’t enroll you from the waitlist
Reason: Available seats are reserved and you do not meet any requirements for the reserved seats."
Is the class gonna expand more? Should I be worried?
history.subject: "Enrollment Update: Can’t enroll you from the waitlist"

history.content:
I got an email titled :
"Enrollment Update: Can’t enroll you from the waitlist
Reason: Available seats are reserved and you do not meet any requirements for the reserved seats."

But students who were just a few spots before me have been enrolled even tho I was in lab lite. Is the class gonna expand more ? Should I be worried?
